**A JavaScript `debounce` function limits how often a function can be called.**

```javascript
function debounce(func, delay) {
    let debounceTimer;
    return function() {
        const context = this;
        const args = arguments;
        clearTimeout(debounceTimer);
        debounceTimer = setTimeout(() => func.apply(context, args), delay);
    };
}

// Example usage:
const handleInput = debounce((event) => {
    console.log('Input changed:', event.target.value);
}, 300);

const inputElement = document.getElementById('exampleInput');
inputElement.addEventListener('input', handleInput);
```

**Example:** This debounced `handleInput` function will log the new input value only after the user has stopped typing for 300 milliseconds.
